          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Moroccans protest
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/palestine-support-protests-rabat-morocco-israel-gaza-war.png" alt="Demonstrators march to express support for Palestinians amid the 2023 Israel-Gaza war in Rabat, Morocco" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Demonstrators march to express support for Palestinians amid the 2023 Israel-Gaza war in Rabat, Morocco. Credits: FADEL SENNA/AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          In one of the largest demonstrations in months, Moroccans protested in Rabat against <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-h1-1-israels-military-campaign" target="_blank" >Israel’s military campaign</a> in Gaza and US support for the war. Protesters condemned the destruction in Gaza over the last 18 months. They also held images of slain Hamas leaders, trampled on Israeli flags, and denounced President Trump’s controversial proposal to relocate Palestinians forcibly.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Organizers accused Israel of ethnic cleansing, citing over 50,700 Palestinian deaths since the war began. Many are angry about Morocco’s 2020 decision to normalize ties with Israel through the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-h3-4-was-reelected" target="_blank" >Abraham Accords</a>. There have also been rallies across the Middle East and North Africa, including Tunisia and Yemen.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Protesters criticized Trump and Biden, some seeing little difference in their policies. Moroccan authorities tolerated demonstrations, though activists linking criticism to the monarchy or foreign missions faced arrests. Many Moroccans continue to oppose Israel despite official diplomatic relations between the two countries.</p>
        </mj-text>
