          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">US-Israel bi-lateral talk</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/trump-netanyahu-meeting-oval-office-white-house-washington-dc.png" alt="US President Donald Trump meets with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in the Oval Office of the White House in Washington, DC" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>US President Donald Trump meets with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in the Oval Office of the White House in Washington, DC. Credits: SAUL LOEB / AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">President Donald Trump and Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu met at the White House on Monday afternoon. The discussion touched upon various topics, including:</p>
          <ol style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5; margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:5px;">
            <li>Israel’s push for reduced tariffs</li>
            <li>Closing Iran’s nuclear program</li>
            <li>Ceasefire in Gaza</li>
            <li>Ease Israel-Turkey tensions</li>
          </ol>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israel suggested it <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-h2-3-would-erase-the-trade-deficit" target="_blank">would erase the trade deficit</a> to abstain from the sweeping tariffs. However, Trump dismissed this idea, citing the $4B spent on Israel, mostly in military aid. Israel is currently facing 17% tariffs.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Before the meeting, Trump spoke with French President Emmanuel Macron, Egyptian President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi, and King Abdullah II of Jordan. These leaders are key mediators in establishing peace in the Middle East. Trump asserted that the next round of hostage-ceasefire agreements should be established and assured that he would work to ease tensions between Israel and Turkey.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Trump also recently wrote a letter to Iran’s supreme leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, seeking direct talks to abandon their nuclear program. However, Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian dismissed Trump’s idea while keeping the indirect talks open.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
