        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Turkey reelects leader Özgür Özel </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: Opposition CHP reelects leader Özgür Özel as he rallies national and international support against President Erdoğan </strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The center-left CHP (Republican People’s Party) leader Özgür Özel <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-h3-4-was-reelected" target="_blank" >was reelected</a> as the party’s Chairman to add pressure on President Erdoğan over the jailing of Istanbul Mayor and presidential candidate Ekrem Imamoğlu. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Imamoğlu’s detention over a terrorism and corruption charge triggered <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-h3-5-turkeys-largest-protest" target="_blank" >Turkey’s largest protests</a> in a decade, drawing many people, including students. Nearly 2,000 people have been detained, with around 300 jailed. The CHP, denouncing the charges as politically motivated, plans to stage weekly nationwide rallies demanding his release and early elections. Özel declared that over 7 million signatures had been gathered in support.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">According to some polls, Imamoğlu could defeat Erdoğan in the next election, which nearly 15 million CHP members endorsed. Critics accuse Erdoğan of eroding democracy and squashing dissent. The CHP recently dominated local elections, grabbing Istanbul and Ankara, and is expanding its national influence. Interestingly enough, Erdogan has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-h3-6-received-much-support" target="_blank" >received much support</a> from Turks outside Turkey.  </p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
