          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇺🇸 US to revoke all visas for South Sudanese over repatriation row</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">US Secretary of State Marco Rubio announced the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-br1-7-revocation-of-visas" target="_blank" >revocation of visas</a> for all South Sudanese nationals as the country refused to accept deported citizens from the US. Rubio stated that South Sudanese will also be blocked at US entry points, accusing the transitional government of exploiting US immigration policies.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The move aligns with President Trump’s focus on mass deportations. Temporary Protected Status for South Sudanese is set to become void on May 3rd. The decision raises concerns as tensions and fear of civil war are increasing in South Sudan. The visa ban will impact figures like Duke University basketball star Khaman Maluach, originally from South Sudan.</p>
