          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇫🇷 Le Pen’s ‘Save Democracy’ rally after guilty verdict falls short of expectations</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Marine Le Pen’s “Save Democracy” <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-04-2025-br2-8-rally-in-paris" target="_blank" >rally in Paris</a> drew a smaller-than-expected crowd after her conviction for embezzling EU funds and a five-year ban from running for office. Despite favorable weather and heavy promotion, attendance was low.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Le Pen claimed the ruling was politically motivated and attacked EU institutions, comparing her struggle to that of Martin Luther King Jr. Left-wing groups counterprotested to defend the rule of law. While Le Pen’s electoral support remains strong, polls show most French voters back the court’s decision and view it as a sign of judicial independence.</p>
        </mj-text>
